Definition.WordDefinition: outback \outback\ n. The remote bush country of Australia; as, they hunted kangaroo in the outback. [Australian] [WordNet 1.5]

Definition.WordDefinition:
outback \outback\ adj. same as {out-of-the-way}. [prenominal]
Syn: backwoods(prenominal), out-of-the-way, remote. [WordNet 1.5]
outback adj : inaccessible and sparsely populated [syn: {backwoods(a)}, {outback(a)}, {remote}] n : the bush country of the interior of Australia
